@startuml
!theme vibrant

title Shelfbot Application Micro-ROS Communication Flow

autonumber "<b>[0]"

box "ROS 2 Computer" #LightBlue
    participant "Shelfbot Application" as Shelfbot
    participant "micro-ROS Agent" as Agent
end box

box "Microcontroller" #LightGreen
    participant "ESP32-CAM Firmware" as Firmware
end box

== 1. Setup & Discovery ==
Firmware -> Agent: Establish UDP Connection
activate Firmware
activate Agent
Agent -> Agent: Create Client Session
Agent --> Firmware: Acknowledge Session

note right of Agent
  The Agent now creates ROS 2 entities
  (Node, Publishers, Subscribers)
  on behalf of the Firmware. These
  become discoverable on the ROS 2 network.
end note
deactivate Agent

... 5 seconds later ...

Shelfbot -> Shelfbot: Discover `/camera/image_raw/compressed` topic
activate Shelfbot
Shelfbot -> Agent: Subscribe to topic
deactivate Shelfbot

== 2. Image Data Stream (Loop) ==
Firmware -> Firmware: Capture Frame
Firmware -> Agent: Publish `CompressedImage` message
activate Agent
Agent -> Shelfbot: Forward `CompressedImage` message
activate Shelfbot
Shelfbot -> Shelfbot: Process Image (AprilTag, SLAM, Obstacles)
deactivate Shelfbot
deactivate Agent

== 3. LED Control Command (Example) ==
Shelfbot -> Agent: Publish `Bool` message to `/camera/led`
activate Shelfbot
activate Agent
Agent -> Firmware: Forward `Bool` message
Firmware -> Firmware: Execute LED Callback
deactivate Agent
deactivate Shelfbot
deactivate Firmware

@enduml